chunk_content: Indicator changes • Added a new numerator disaggregate “Recently Tested Negatives" to better account for HIV (MER v2.6.1 to v2.7): testing coverage among various sub-groups among individuals with TB disease. Reporting level: Facility Reporting Quarterly frequency: How to use: This indicator measures the performance of the TB program in ensuring that TB cases know their HIV status. How to collect: The numerator and denominator can be obtained from basic management unit TB registers as well as additional data collection sources (i.e., HIV testing registers) that may contain relevant information (i.e., HIV test results, enrollment in HIV care programs).
